riddles:
Before I went a-questing,
I was but a simple tree;
'Til once an artificer came,
And cut myself from me;
The energies in me infused,
I cannot understand;
But take my firmly in thy grip,
And lightning you'll command.

I don't quite belong here,
That much is clear;
The brochure understated,
The peril and fear;
But I set to make the best of it,
And site-see what I can;
I took lots of photos,
Of the things from which I ran.

Be careful, brave adventurer, should you and I e'er meet;
For e'en should you vanquish me (to be clear: quite the feat);
I shan't e'en then be through with you; I'll catch you unawares;
Take caution all who'd wield my flesh: thine enemy is stairs.

Value me as you do life,
For what I am is you;
And if perchance some loot should drop,
We'll both get something new;
I may be limited in scope,
Or by what you'll endure;
In either case our goal's the same:
To live is to procure.
